Registration for Entrance Examination into the Nigerian Military School, Zaria has commenced online. The application will close on May 29, 2021. A statement signed by the Permanent Secretary, Cabinet and Special Services Department, Governor’s Office, Mr. Adedayo Ajobiewe, advised candidates to visit the school’s website, fill their forms and make payment using their Bank ATM cards. The statement stressed that applicants must be at least 12 years old and not more than 14 years by September 2021, adding that the admission is only open to male Nigerians who fulfil the given entry requirements. It advised candidates to print clear and clean copies of their application forms, payment advice slips and examination photo cards